verses.text: I will love thee, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, my strength. \q1

The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* my rock , and my fortress , and my deliverer ; my God , my strength , in whom I will trust ; my buckler , and the horn of my salvation , \add and\add* my high tower.\f + \fr 18.2 \ft my strength: Heb. my rock\f* \q1
I will call upon the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add who is worthy\add* to be praised : so shall I be saved from mine enemies. \q1
The sorrows of death compassed me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.\f + \fr 18.4 \ft ungodly men: Heb. Belial\f* \q1
The sorrows of hell compassed me about : the snares of death prevented me.\f + \fr 18.5 \ft sorrows: or, cords\f* \q1
In my distress I called upon the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and cried unto my God : he heard my voice out of his temple , and my cry came before him, \add even\add* into his ears. \q1
Then the earth shook and trembled ; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken , because he was wroth. \q1
There went up a smoke out of his nostrils , and fire out of his mouth devoured : coals were kindled by it.\f + \fr 18.8 \ft out of his nostrils: Heb. by his, etc\f* \q1
He bowed the heavens also, and came down : and darkness \add was\add* under his feet. \q1
And he rode upon a cherub , and did fly : yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind. \q1
He made darkness his secret place ; his pavilion round about him \add were\add* dark waters \add and\add* thick clouds of the skies. \q1
At the brightness \add that was\add* before him his thick clouds passed , hail \add stones\add* and coals of fire. \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* also thundered in the heavens , and the Highest gave his voice ; hail \add stones\add* and coals of fire. \q1
Yea, he sent out his arrows , and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings , and discomfited them. \q1
Then the channels of waters were seen , and the foundations of the world were discovered at thy rebuke , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, at the blast of the breath of thy nostrils. \q1
He sent from above , he took me, he drew me out of many waters.\f + \fr 18.16 \ft many: or, great\f* \q1
He delivered me from my strong enemy , and from them which hated me: for they were too strong for me. \q1
They prevented me in the day of my calamity : but the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* was my stay. \q1
He brought me forth also into a large place ; he delivered me, because he delighted in me. \b \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* rewarded me according to my righteousness ; according to the cleanness of my hands hath he recompensed me. \q1
For I have kept the ways of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, and have not wickedly departed from my God. \q1
For all his judgments \add were\add* before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me. \q1
I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from mine iniquity.\f + \fr 18.23 \ft before: Heb. with\f* \q1

Therefore hath the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* recompensed me according to my righteousness , according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.\f + \fr 18.24 \ft in…: Heb. before his eyes\f* \q1
With the merciful thou wilt shew thyself merciful ; with an upright man thou wilt shew thyself upright ; \q1
With the pure thou wilt shew thyself pure ; and with the froward thou wilt shew thyself froward.\f + \fr 18.26 \ft shew thyself froward: or, wrestle\f* \q1
For thou wilt save the afflicted people ; but wilt bring down high looks. \q1
For thou wilt light my candle : the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* my God will enlighten my darkness.\f + \fr 18.28 \ft candle: or, lamp\f* \b \q1
For by thee I have run through a troop ; and by my God have I leaped over a wall.\f + \fr 18.29 \ft run…: or, broken\f* \q1

\add As for\add* God , his way \add is\add* perfect : the word of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* is tried : he \add is\add* a buckler to all those that trust in him.\f + \fr 18.30 \ft tried: or, refined\f* \q1
For who \add is\add* God save the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*? or who \add is\add* a rock save our God ? \q1
\add It is\add* God that girdeth me with strength , and maketh my way perfect. \q1
He maketh my feet like hinds’ \add feet\add*, and setteth me upon my high places. \q1
He teacheth my hands to war , so that a bow of steel is broken by mine arms. \q1

Thou hast also given me the shield of thy salvation : and thy right hand hath holden me up , and thy gentleness hath made me great.\f + \fr 18.35 \ft thy gentleness…: or, with thy meekness thou hast multiplied me\f* \q1
Thou hast enlarged my steps under me, that my feet did not slip.\f + \fr 18.36 \ft my feet: Heb. mine ankles\f* \q1
I have pursued mine enemies , and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed. \q1
I have wounded them that they were not able to rise : they are fallen under my feet. \q1
For thou hast girded me with strength unto the battle : thou hast subdued under me those that rose up against me.\f + \fr 18.39 \ft subdued: Heb. caused to bow\f* \q1
Thou hast also given me the necks of mine enemies ; that I might destroy them that hate me. \q1
They cried , but \add there was\add* none to save \add them: even\add* unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, but he answered them not. \q1
Then did I beat them small as the dust before the wind : I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets. \q1
Thou hast delivered me from the strivings of the people ; \add and\add* thou hast made me the head of the heathen : a people \add whom\add* I have not known shall serve me. \q1

As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the strangers shall submit themselves unto me.\f + \fr 18.44 \ft As soon…: Heb. At the hearing of the ear\f*\f + \fr 18.44 \ft submit…: or, yield feigned obedience\f*\f + \fr 18.44 \ft strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger\f* \q1
The strangers shall fade away , and be afraid out of their close places.\f + \fr 18.45 \ft strangers: Heb. sons of the stranger\f* \q1
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* liveth ; and blessed \add be\add* my rock ; and let the God of my salvation be exalted. \q1
\add It is\add* God that avengeth me, and subdueth the people under me.\f + \fr 18.47 \ft avengeth: Heb. giveth avengements for\f*\f + \fr 18.47 \ft subdueth: or, destroyeth\f* \q1
He delivereth me from mine enemies : yea, thou liftest me up above those that rise up against me: thou hast delivered me from the violent man.\f + \fr 18.48 \ft violent…: Heb. man of violence\f* \q1
Therefore will I give thanks unto thee, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, among the heathen , and sing praises unto thy name.\f + \fr 18.49 \ft give…: or, confess\f* \q1
Great deliverance giveth he to his king ; and sheweth mercy to his anointed , to David , and to his seed for evermore.
